The paper deals with the problem of learning an overcomplete dictionary for sparse representation from a large training dataset, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. The application of the proposed algorithm is in image denoising, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm also involves parallel processing, which is a common technique in distributed computing and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithm in terms of memory and computational complexity, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with image and video analytics, which are subfields of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for dictionary learning, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
